THEN AND NOW
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    In 1937, with clear signs that Nazi Germany was preparing for war
    and mindful of the horrors inflicted by poison gas during World War
    1, the British government decided to issue all 38 million civilian
    members of the UK population with gas masks. To this end they set
    up a factory in a disused mill in Blackburn, Lancashire.

